The Herald Conrad Mupesa Mashonaland West Bureau A driver of a Toyota Mark X died on the spot in Chinhoyi in the early hours of today after failing to negotiate a curve along the Chinhoyi-Chegutu highway and went on to ram a big tree. A passenger, believed to be his wife, sustained serious injuries and is admitted at Chinhoyi Provincial Hospital. The driver had driven less than 2 kilometres from a local popular entertainment joint in Chinhoyi.